    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/478.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Consul <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to previous instructions directing you to report facts to Department
                    before taking action for protection of Spaniards, you are now authorized in
                    cases where in your opinion prompt action is needed, to extend friendly good
                    offices on behalf Spaniards before receiving Department’s instructions in
                    particular cases.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
